Sri Lanka Builds 112-Run Lead Against Australia in Third Test in Colombo

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-09-18T13:15:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/sri-lanka-builds-112-run-lead-against-australia-in-third-test-in-colombo.html
Sri Lanka  ended day three of the
third cricket Test against Australia with a 112-run lead as it
targets a victory to tie the series.  Angelo Mathews was 85 not out as the hosts reached 428-6 in
their first innings in Colombo, with Shaminda Eranga unbeaten on
5. Tillakaratne Dilshan hit 83, while Kumar Sangakkara and
Mahela Jayawardene also got half-centuries.  Mathews shared a 121-run fifth-wicket partnership with
Dilshan to take Sri Lanka past Australiaâ€™s total of 316 all out,
then combined with Prasanna Jayawardene for 81 runs.  Australia won the opener of the three-game series by 125
runs, while the second Test was drawn. Australia will move above
Sri Lanka to fourth in the International Cricket Council  Test
rankings  by winning the series.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in London at   jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 